channel.title: Working a no-ip
channel.description:
Have a server. Yes I have a server on no-ip. I go into webclient. Type in the server: LegendScape.no-ip.info
And I get "no response, choose another world"
I have the DNS client also.
Any idea what is wrong?

item.title: Working a no-ip
item.dc:creator: @Legend1 -Legend-
item.description:
@Legend1 wrote:

[quote=“Tico135, post:2, topic:93421”]In your server file, go to “run” and double click it. Make sure you know the port. Check it by going into your “server.java” file and looking for a line like this:

public static int serverlistenerPort = 43594; //43594=default

Look at what the number is. For me it is 43594. See what yours is and make sure that that is what you are entering.[/quote]

My run.bat file is empty for no reason. Copy and paste the entire thing that is suppose to be written in run.bat and post here please

item.title: Working a no-ip
item.dc:creator: @Tico135 Tico
item.description:
@Tico135 wrote:

In your server file, go to “run” and double click it. Make sure you know the port. Check it by going into your “server.java” file and looking for a line like this:

public static int serverlistenerPort = 43594; //43594=default

Look at what the number is. For me it is 43594. See what yours is and make sure that that is what you are entering.
